# Line endings are this repo's to decide, not each machine's core.autocrlf.
# Orthanc is built on both macOS and Windows, so leaving the choice to whatever
# a given checkout happens to be configured for means the same file reads as
# modified on one machine and clean on another.
#
# LF everywhere — in the repository and in the working tree alike. Flutter
# regenerates its plugin registrants with LF on every `pub get`, so a working
# tree held at CRLF leaves those files perpetually dirty on Windows for a
# difference that is not a difference. Nothing here needs CRLF: no .bat, .cmd
# or .ps1 files are tracked, and the Windows runner already builds from LF —
# Runner.rc and runner.exe.manifest are stored that way, and Visual Studio
# Community 2022 compiled them without complaint.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries git must never rewrite. Its content detection already spares these,
# but say so plainly rather than trust a heuristic with the app's icons. These
# are the only binary types the tree holds today; add a line when another
# arrives rather than leaving it to the heuristic alone.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
